### Setting up the Development Environment
To set up the development environment, follow these steps:
1. Install the STM32CubeMX tool.
2. Install the STM32CubeIDE tool.
3. Install the STM32CubeMonitor tool.
4. Install the STM32CubeProgrammer tool.
5. Configure the development board.
6. Create a new project in the STM32CubeMX tool.
7. Generate the code for the project.
8. Build and debug the project using the STM32CubeIDE tool.

### Example Code
The following example code can be used to blink an LED connected to a GPIO pin:
```c
#include "stm32f4xx.h"

int main() {
  // Initialize the GPIO pin
  GPIO_InitTypeDef gpio_init;
  gpio_init.Pin = GPIO_PIN_5;
  gpio_init.Mode = GPIO_MODE_OUTPUT;
  gpio_init.Pull = GPIO_NOPULL;
  gpio_init.Speed = GPIO_SPEED_FREQ_HIGH;
  HAL_GPIO_Init(GPIOA, &gpio_init);

  while (1) {
    // Turn the LED on
    HAL_GPIO_WritePin(GPIOA, GPIO_PIN_5, GPIO_PIN_SET);
    HAL_Delay(1000);

    // Turn the LED off
    HAL_GPIO_WritePin(GPIOA, GPIO_PIN_5, GPIO_PIN_RESET);
    HAL_Delay(1000);
  }

  return 0;
}
